The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, June 19: Spice Communications has fixed the price band of its public issue between Rs 41 and Rs 46 per equity share of Rs 10 each. We recently concluded a pre-ipo placement of 24,837,889 shares at Rs 45 per share, thereby raising about Rs 112 crore. A clutch of investors led by Lehman Brothers and Sinnaker Investments have picked up a small stake in Spice Telecom, company chairman and managing director Dilip Modi said.

 New Delhi, June 19: The government has simplified the service tax rules to replace the current circulars. Two draft circulars on technical and procedural issues were posted on the website of the Central Board of Excise and Customs. 

 New Delhi, June 19: The coal ministry will approve another 15 blocks with reserves of 3,500 million tonnes. Of these, five are in Jharkhand, three in Orissa, five in Chhattisgarh and two in Bengal.

 New Delhi, June 19: Companies paid

 Rs 13,796 crore as advance tax till June 18 this fiscal.

 This is 28.6 per cent higher than last year. The governments

 direct tax kitty swelled by Rs 37,444 crore.

 Postdam, June 19: The

 four key players in the World

 Trade Organisation the US, the

 European Union, Brazil and India met

 today for critical talks to break

 the deadlock over a global trade

 deal.




